    "caption": "Tiny explorer with whiskers that feel every gap before squeezing through.",
    "shortDescription": "A mouse uses its whiskers like a ruler — before squeezing into any hole, it checks the width first. Those wiry little whiskers brush the edges and tell the mouse's brain whether it's a go or a no. Mice can fit through any gap big enough for a pencil to pass through. Fun fact: A mouse's whiskers can feel air movements to detect danger even in complete darkness."
